Pronotum arched, widest at base (pl/pw = 0.61-0.65); slightly narrowing toward apex; lateral margin thickened anteriorly; pronotal anterior margin normal, not projecting forward beyond anterior angles (typical for the subgenus 
Xenodacne
). Pronotum distinctly punctured medially, finely and closely punctured laterally.

Diagnosis. Dacne tangliangi is most similar to Dacne (Xenodacne) maculata Chujo due to similar form and color pattern of the body. Dacne tangliangi can be distinguished from Dacne maculata by the black pronotum, scutellum not transverse (length/width<1.5), posterior band in elytron not extending to the border and occurs in southwest China. Dacne maculata has a reddish pronotum, scutellum transverse (length/width>1.5), posterior band in elytron extending to the border and occurs in Japan and Siberia (
Chujo and Chujo 1988
).
